ed -> tool.completed(error)` with no `tool.started`.\\n+- [ ] Duplicate IDs, missing classification, and non-allowlisted tools still fail closed.\\n+- [ ] Cancellation reaches the executing tool; the timeout wrapper does not merely abandon a still-running promise.\\n+- [ ] No MCP SDK, MCP config, network transport, or MCP-specific type enters this PR.\\n+\\n+**Why separate:** This is cross-cutting execution infrastructure with regression risk to the only shipped tool. Review it without MCP lifecycle noise.\\n+\\n+## T1 — instance-managed remote Streamable HTTP MCP tools\\n+\\n+**Action:** Create as a sub-issue of rewritten #40; blocked by T0.\\n+\\n+**Labels:** `enhancement`, `mcp`, `infra`\\n+\\n+**Outcome:** An operator configures remote Streamable HTTP MCP servers. Explicitly declared read-only tools become namespaced entries in the existing Run tool catalog; unavailable servers degrade only their own tools.\\n+\\n+**Owned production surface:**\\n+\\n+- MCP configuration in `apps/api/src/instance-config/`\\n+- `apps/api/llame.config.json.example`\\n+- new `apps/api/src/mcp/` module, manager, and adapter\\n+- `apps/api/package.json` and `pnpm-lock.yaml`\\n+- minimal catalog/module wiring from T0\\n+- protocol and Run integration tests\\n+\\n+**Scope:**\\n+\\n+- Add strict instance config for remote servers, interpolated headers, stable server IDs, and operator-declared `readOnlyTools`.\\n+- Pin `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@^1.29`; Streamable HTTP only.\\n+- Namespace IDs as `__mcp__<serverId>__<toolName>` and keep them compatible with `tools.allowed`.\\n+- Reuse one client/transport per server only in a runs-consuming worker.\\n+- Perform bounded, paginated discovery and atomically publish a safe catalog snapshot.\\n+- Compile MCP input JSON Schemas once during discovery with Ajv 2020-12 plus formats.\\n+- Keep ordinary chats/native tools immediately available when an MCP server is offline; reconnect in bounded single-flight background attempts.\\n+- Map MCP content