n+- [ ] Refresh/history replay reconstructs the same tool activity and final answer.\\n+- [ ] Environment-gated real remote web-search MCP eval returns current sourced evidence without logging credentials.\\n+- [ ] No production runtime behavior is expanded in this issue; defects found in T1 return to T1 unless they are purely acceptance plumbing.\\n+\\n+**Relationship to #179:** Cross-link it, but do not block T0 or T1. If this issue reproduces #179's `Chat.makeRequest(...state)` refresh signature, stop adding retries and repair #179 as its own issue before declaring T2 complete.\\n+\\n+## E0 — narrow existing #198 to the episodic MVP\\n+\\n+**Action:** Rewrite #198 instead of creating another memory issue. Keep it under #194 and assign it to milestone #5.\\n+\\n+**Labels:** Keep `enhancement`, `knowledge`, `security`.\\n+\\n+**Outcome:** Turn the already-shipped `search_conversations` tool into a deterministic, safely framed agent-recall acceptance path.\\n+\\n+**Scope:**\\n+\\n+- Frame recalled excerpts as historical data that may be stale and never as new instructions.\\n+- Add one minimal prompt/tool-description hint for explicit references to past discussions or missing past context.\\n+- Add a deterministic two-Chat acceptance: Chat A records an unusual decision; Chat B deliberately recalls it.\\n+- Reassert trusted Run identity and cross-tenant isolation.\\n+- Test instruction-shaped text inside recalled chat content.\\n+\\n+**Acceptance:**\\n+\\n+- [ ] Chat B calls `search_conversations` and answers the unique decision from Chat A.\\n+- [ ] Returned instruction-shaped content remains visibly bounded as historical data.\\n+- [ ] Cross-tenant chat content is absent.\\n+- [ ] Existing search result fields and web search behavior remain compatible.\\n+- [ ] No embeddings, auto-injection, natural-language temporal parser, recency decay, or new memory store.\\n+\\n+**Moved out of #198:** Temporal filtering, richer message-range provenance, recency ranking, and `matchedBy`-driven semantics return to #194's future backlog. Do not immediately create replacement issues; file them only when retrieval evals justify the work.\\n+\\n+## K0 — read-only personal Markdown vault\\n+\\n+**Action:** Create as a sub-issue of rewritten #39; blocked by T0, not by live MCP availability.\\n+\\n+**Labels:** `enhancement`, `knowledge`, `security`\\n+\\n+**Outcome:** The agent can search and read a user's canonical Git-backed Markdown vault through ordinary tools, with no Postgres knowledge copy or embeddings.\\n+\\n+**Owned production surface:**\\n+\\n+- Home/vault instance config\\n+- new `apps/api/src/knowledge/` module, paths, vault service, and tools\\n+- worker module/mount wiring\\n+- `apps/api/src/chats/context-builder.ts`\\n+- `apps/api/src/tools/tool-catalog.service.ts` registration only\\n+- `flake.nix` Git runtime declaration\\n+- focused unit/integration and browser acceptance\\n+\\n+**Scope:**\\n+\\n+- Derive a path-safe user storage key as `base64url(sha256(userId))` under one operator-configured Home root.\\n+- Treat a service-owned Git repository and accepted ref as canonical; create a safe empty repo/bootstrap commit on first use or accept a valid existing repo at the exact location.\\n+- Read blobs from the accepted ref; uncommitted editor/agent work stays invisible.\\n+- Provide bounded direct-scan `knowledge_search` and paged `knowledge_read` tools.\\n+- Reject traversal, absolute paths, non-Markdown blobs, oversized operations, and all symlinks.\\n+- Return path, content/blob hash, accepted commit, snippets/content, and paging metadata.\\n+- Tell the model that notes are potentially stale, untrusted data; volatile claims should be verified with external tools.\\n+- Ensure API and dedicated worker share the persistent Home volume; never mount the host home.\\n+\\n+**Acceptance:**\\n+\\n+- [ ] Two users with the same keyword retrieve only their own note.\\n+- [ ] Raw/path-shaped user IDs, traversal, symlinks, oversized vaults