te; source volatile claims.\\n+\\n+**Acceptance:**\\n+\\n+- [ ] Research result creates one note and exactly one commit.\\n+- [ ] Correction with the expected hash creates one later commit; stale hash changes nothing.\\n+- [ ] Full Run retry with different regenerated args cannot create a second effect.\\n+- [ ] Crash before commit, after commit, after accepted-ref publication, and during checkout synchronization each reconcile deterministically.\\n+- [ ] Concurrent writers serialize and stale writers conflict.\\n+- [ ] Empty `HOME`/missing global Git identity does not break service commits.\\n+- [ ] A new Chat reads the landed note.\\n+- [ ] No multi-file patch, Jujutsu, automatic LLM review/merge, background human-edit watcher, shared KB, or generic remote write tool.\\n+\\n+**Why not split:** The Git service, write tool, dedupe protocol, cancellation, and crash tests are one safety claim. Merging any subset first would advertise a write capability whose correctness has not been proved.\\n+\\n+## R0 — combined runnable-agent release gate\\n+\\n+**Action:** Create as a sub-issue of rewritten #39; blocked by T2, E0, and K1.\\n+\\n+**Labels:** `mcp`, `knowledge`, `runs`, `documentation`\\n+\\n+**Outcome:** Prove the compounding product loop, not merely three isolated subsystems.\\n+\\n+**Scope:**\\n+\\n+- Reuse T2's local MCP fixture and model dispatcher.\\n+- Use a temporary per-user Git vault plus real Postgres/RLS and queued worker.\\n+- In Chat A, search current evidence through MCP and retain a sourced Markdown note.\\n+- Refresh/reopen during the Run and reconstruct MCP/KB tool activity.\\n+- In Chat B, retrieve the note from the KB and cite its path/source URLs.\\n+- In Chat C, recall what happened in Chat A through `search_conversations`.\\n+- Add an environment-gated real-model/real-search eval judged only on observable dispatch, evidence use, note quality, later retrieval, and unsupported claims.\\n+- Reconcile `ROADMAP.md`, `VISION.md`, relevant tracker bo